<p> <h5> <center> Risks </h5> </center> </p>

<p> 

Risks are the facts that discourages a project where the team members must face and overcome it. Decisions make risks more powerful and sometimes avoid them without any problem. Developing an application is not an easy task but not a task which we cannot achieve with right products and people. Unfortunately, there are some risks that we will have to face while developing our project as team members.

</p>

<p>

Biggest risk of developing applications is the targeted users who does not want the application. If the chosen target user group refuses the app, it will be the biggest risk that can happen to a project. To avoid this risk, we should consider more about our targeted users and see from their perspective. It will attract the targeted user group to the app and the app will satisfy them gaining more users.

</p>

<p>

Choosing the app developer is another risk for the app as this decision will impact the whole project itself. Wrong App Developer can ruin whole project in a minute, and it will be a disaster to face as a team who are developing an application. We should consider more about the quality of the work of the App developer before choosing him for the project and we should not rely on cost more at this stage.

</p>

<p>

Risk of data security should overcome by enhancing more security strategies such as OpenID Connect, Oauth2 for safe logins. Also, encryption systems and security layers should be implemented to secure the users while using the application. App integration, Anti debugging will help more to secure the data of the app users for the developers when they develop the application.

</p>	

